cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with neural networks and their representations, which are typically studied in the machine learning and computer vision communities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the non-linear nature of neural networks, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses image datasets and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
